o not allow private investment alone.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Going forward, effort should be focussed on enabling the development and realisation of innovation in a clear and simple landscape.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We believe that the Government</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> should</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, through </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">evidence based selection,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> foster </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">innovation in all l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ow carbon technologies that are key to deliver</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing a decarbonised economy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. In addition, it should help underpin technolo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">gies such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">IT and d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">igital</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> media</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SMEs have a critical role in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> innovation supply chain</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and they should be proactively supported</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not only in the development of technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> but also in forming commercial relationship</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with the entir</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e supply chain and the investor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> community.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government has a role in continuing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">financial support of innovation through bodies such as the Research Councils and TSB. The Research Councils have the unique role </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> nurtur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the skill set and the research base that ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a vital role in the innovation cycle. TSB initiatives allow a measur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e of risk</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sharing that is essential in technological developments</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">wever</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> more should be done to demonstrate innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> because without this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, innovative technologies or services will not be taken up. Initiatives such as ‘Innovative Refurb’ to demonstrate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> energy efficiency technologies for the industrial and commercial sector are examples of demonstrators that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Government can support.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The timescales involved in low carbon innova</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tion are long and progress is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> often incremental. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The private sector needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">long</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">certaint</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to invest in innovation. The Government should consider ways to encourage and incentivise the establishment of long</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">term provision of skills and continuity of innovation programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">both in the public and private sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to address this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> issue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It should ensure that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ideas are appropriately developed, assessed, filtered and taken through to adoption. Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is would have the added benefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of creating new</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> highly skilled jobs and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> other spill</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">over benefits to the economy.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-si