ze:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EDF Energy has contributed to the Technology Innovation Needs </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Assessment (TINA) project, led by the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> LCICG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he resulting documents are reasonably balanced, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> broadly supportive of the key conclusions. However, the results do not seem to have been widely communicated.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Whil</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the LCICG TINA work has been posit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ive, there does not appear to be an overarching strategy in place, or at least one that has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">been clearly communicated, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">outlines </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the role of all</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enewa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ble and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ow </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">arbon technologies. It is important that a broader strategy is developed to help align s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">takeholders and existing/future programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EDF Energy recommends that t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">his strategy should be widely communicated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ordinated with other programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. This should be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">underpinned with a work programme and a set of deliverables that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ndustry has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">both </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">contributed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and agreed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Funding Mechanisms</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We believe that the approach to releasing funds for the low carbon network funds (LCNF) could provide a solid base from which to establish innovation funding arrangements. The key areas to learn from this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">regime were:</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Tiered approach to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">collaborative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">project funding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – with a simpler approach taken for lower value </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and a more complex approach with greater scrutiny for projects above a threshold. This</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> method</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ensured that smaller projects were not discouraged from requesting funding due to the complexities and bureaucracy with their requests</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> It</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> also ensur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that higher value projects were subject to sufficient scrutiny to ensure they provided value for money f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or projects.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Stable regime and process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> – although there was a steep learning curve for the initial projects, having a stable regime and process help</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> facilitate subsequent funding requests and applications</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as participants became accustomed to what was req</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uired</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">when. </span></li></ol></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is also worth ensuring that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">funding is available to a wide range of participants from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uppliers through to technological innovation firms. A </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">downside</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of the LCNF regime was that it also required </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Distribution Network Operator (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">DNO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">participation – this therefore limited funding to projects that the DNOs also had an interest in progressing. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Any innovation funding mechanism should ensure that both the demand and generation side are captured. Focusing solely on one of these may not </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">result in the most cost efficient and effective solution for customers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Nuclear</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ignificant progress has been made by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Government </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and industry </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">with the development of the Nuclear Industry Strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The UK’s Nuclear Future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">establishment of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Nuclear Industry Council.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">EDF Energy is p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ositive about implementing recommendations from the House of Lords Science and Technology Committee on nuclear R&a