</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Whether the GB business case for community energy schemes is positive</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> -</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There have been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ambitious</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">aspirations from ministers and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment regarding the potential </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for community energy schemes to revolutionise the energy market and help realise low carbon targets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">owever, no consideration has been given as to whether they represent value for money</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and a positive business case on an end</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">end basis. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.56pt; padding-left:4.44pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The smart grid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> forum has identified that over the period 20</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">15-2023</s