ly:Arial; font-size:11pt">. With the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">recasted increase in renewable generation,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> measures </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that include </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">energy efficiency, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">load shifting/demand curtailment and demand response</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> will become increasingly important as part of the transition to a low carbon economy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What outcomes, if any, are the LCICG likely to achieve? How should its forthcoming strategy drive more investment in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">to low carbon innovation, and how should it measure success? </span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The forthcoming LCICG strategy is vital in driving more investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hil</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Aria