e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">should take into account </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the le</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ngth of the innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> journey. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be prepared to take risks </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and ensure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">discovery/innovation is not constrained.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There should be a requirement to demonstrate a “commercialisation roadmap” as part of the project establishment/a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pproval process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. We believe that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the end goal should be commercialisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Are the Government &amp; LCICG targeting investment towards the most effective stages of the innovation process, including over the long-term? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="37" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">More focus needs to be placed in bringing innovative technologies to market; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fledging companies and technologies face </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">many hurdles</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and a key challenge i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the ability to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">go from the lab, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to a demonstrator at scale</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and then to the consumer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">More funding sho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uld be made available for large-scale demonstration, testing and commercialisation of innovative technologies. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="38" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Calls for funded projects tend to be issued ad hoc; stakeholders would benefit from longer-term visibility of such calls</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What is the impact of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> the short-term funding timelines on private sector investment? </span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="39" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rivate sector will only invest once </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">potential of innovation starts to become commercial. Short-term funding has b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iggest impact on the R&amp;D sector, how</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ever longer-term support is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">vital to increase private sector confidence.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="40" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Short-term funding can result in a l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ack of certainty </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for the long-term investor and inhibit commercialisation and roll-out, for example in the Heat Pump segment, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in order to drive the technological development </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and also development in skills and business models</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a longer term framework than the RHI is required. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How should DECC ensure that its remaining capital allocation for low carbon innovation will be spent wisely, after two years of underspend? </span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="41" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A panel of energy industry experts could be set-up to advise on allocation. A plan needs to be agreed with industry and academia. Low carbon energy experts could endorse this plan, and monitor against deliverables. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How is the Government maximising opport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">unities to learn from and partner with international partners within and beyond the EU?</span></p><p style="lin